legacy.full_text: #FlyingTigers veteran Harry Moyer, who fought side by side with China against the Japanese invasion during #WorldWarII, turned 103 on Monday, October 30. He celebrated his birthday with family and friends of Flying Tiger veterans by climbing the #GreatWall in #Beijing, China. https://t.co/IGwl1nStkA

He said his birthday wish is “happiness, blessing, and peace throughout the world.” 

The #FlyingTigers is the American Volunteer Group formed in 1941 to help the Chinese Air Forces. To this day, the Flying Tigers are a symbol of friendship between #China and the U.S.

legacy.full_text:
Typhoon #Haikui has lashed historic heavy rain in #HongKong and its neighboring #Shenzhen in southern #China since the evening of Thursday, Sept. 7. Widespread #flooding engulfed businesses and roads, leading to the closure of China’s two top financial hubs on Friday. 
#typhoon https://t.co/Hx2iilmXEq

The ongoing downpour has broken four rainfall records in #Shenzhen since 1952 and has become the heaviest torrential rain in #HongKong for more than 140 years. In HongKong, some low-lying shopping centers are almost completely submerged in muddy #floodwaters. #typhoon #China

legacy.full_text: How did a river in #Tianjin become #China’s most popular tourist destination due to a group of half-naked elderly locals? An influx of visitors across China, including foreign tourists, have been leaning on the railings to watch the “bold performance” by “senior #divers.” https://t.co/K5IozvLX0R

On Shizilin Bridge, the spotlight is on a group of #Tianjin amateur divers, most of whom are in or past their 60s. They have created a new place of interest by making a funny speech to the audience before the plunge, embodying Tianjin’s signature crosstalk comedy, “#Xiangsheng.”
